{
  "stem": "8962.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now you have air letters.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it was very difficult to tear the family apart.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My father was still in Furth at that time, but when the doorbell rang, you never knew who was there, and there was no escape from this apartment house that we lived in.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was one exit, and there was another exit that went into a place in the back where you cleaned your carpets twice a year.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But if the Nazis would have come, you just couldn't escape.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wasn't a child anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You grew up fast.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was 15 then when she left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It sort of broke my heart, but I at that time said I would never leave my parents because I probably could have gone to Palestine too because I belonged to these Jewish organizations.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I forget what they're called.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Haganah?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "No, it was something else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But we would meet, and we would talk about Palestine and what we would do if we would go there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, I wasn't in school anymore, so my Gentile friends didn't talk to me anymore.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Nobody called.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the Gentile people that lived in the apartment house, they would spit at you when they came down, you walked up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So we said this is no good.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We have to go to America.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My father met a young man when he was in the army, and this young man-- this is a different story, but it belongs-- had emigrated to the United States in 1913.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And in 1914, when the war broke out, he was in Germany visiting his parents.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
